## VintageAtlas Cursor Rules

## Critical Constraints

### Vintage Story API Compliance
- **NEVER block the main thread** - use `api.Event.EnqueueMainThreadTask()` for game state access
- All chunk/world access MUST be on main thread via `ICoreServerAPI`
- Extend `ModSystem` class with proper lifecycle (`Start()`, `StartServerSide()`, `Dispose()`)
- Server-side only mod - no client code
- See @vintagestory-modding-constraints for full details

### NixOS Development
- Always use `nix develop` to enter dev shell before running commands
- Use `build-vintageatlas` for release builds (includes frontend)
- Use `quick-test` to build and start test server
- If tool missing: `nix run nixpkgs#{package-name}`

### Build Process
1. Frontend: `cd VintageAtlas/frontend && npm run build`
2. Backend: `dotnet build --configuration Release`
3. Output: `VintageAtlas/bin/Release/Mods/vintageatlas/`

## Project Architecture

### Key Directories
- `Core/` - Configuration, interfaces, utilities
- `Export/` - CPU-intensive map generation (background tasks)
- `Tracking/` - Real-time data collection (main thread)
- `Web/` - HTTP server and API (async)
- `frontend/` - Vue 3 + TypeScript + OpenLayers

### Threading Model
```csharp
// ✅ CORRECT: Background work + main thread callback
Task.Run(() => {
    // Heavy computation here
}).ContinueWith(task => {
    api.Event.EnqueueMainThreadTask(() => {
        // Update game state on main thread
    });
});

// ❌ WRONG: Blocking main thread
Thread.Sleep(5000); // NEVER do this
```

## Coding Standards

### C# Backend
- PascalCase for classes/methods/properties
- Always log errors via `api.Logger` - graceful degradation, never crash
- Never cache chunk data - always request fresh from API
- Reference VS DLLs via VINTAGE_STORY env var (in `Directory.Build.props`)

### TypeScript Frontend
- PascalCase for components/types, camelCase for functions/variables
- Use composition API with `<script setup lang="ts">`
- Properly dispose OpenLayers layers on unmount
- Use centralized `apiClient` for all API calls

### OpenLayers Coordinates
- Game coords: (0,0) at spawn, X=East, Z=South
- Map coords: Web Mercator (EPSG:3857) for display
- Always transform between coordinate systems
- Tiles: Standard XYZ scheme `tiles/{z}/{x}/{y}.png`

